metadata.name: Invocation I
metadata.description:
Society sees Black womxn as strong, powerful, brave, angry and difficult while failing to see their humanity or allowing for them to be seen as vulnerable, gentle, open and compassionate like their white counterparts. 

Symbolically invoking the goddess Kali in this photographic series brings to the fore the contradictions and inherent biases that are present in societiesâ€™ representations of Black womxn.
